    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_8_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_8",
      "description": "Offering a collector-grade 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD, a masterclass in lightweight engineering and rotary performance. This specimen retains its original 13B-REW power plant with factory-spec sequential twin-turbochargers, delivering linear boost and exceptional compression across all rotor faces. The chassis features a perfect 50/50 weight distribution, supported by an unmolested aluminum double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential for surgical turn-in precision. Every vacuum line in the complex 'rat's nest' has been meticulously maintained to ensure flawless transition between primary and secondary boost phases. Zero aftermarket modifications, original paint depth, and a pristine interior make this an investment-grade example of the golden era of Japanese sports cars.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 41
    },
    {
